.TH MILLENNIUM\-PURGE 1 "July 10, 2026" "millennium-helpers" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
millennium-purge \- remove Millennium hooks and client files from Steam
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B millennium-purge
[\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
De-registers Millennium bootstrap hooks from local Steam installs and removes
Millennium system files. This is destructive.
.SH OPTIONS
.\" @@cli-contract:commands.purge.man_options@@
.TP
.BR \-d ", " \-\-dry\-run
Simulate operations without modifying files.
.TP
.BR \-y ", " \-\-yes
Skip the interactive confirmation prompt (required for non-interactive use).
.TP
.BR \-q ", " \-\-quiet
Suppress informational output (warnings and errors still print).
.TP
.BR \-V ", " \-\-version
Show version information.
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Show help message.
.\" @@/cli-contract:commands.purge.man_options@@
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Simulate a purge:
.B sudo millennium-purge --dry-run
.TP
Confirm and remove Millennium:
.B sudo millennium-purge --yes
.TP
Via the dispatcher:
.B sudo millennium purge --yes
.SH NOTES
Requires root on Linux for system-wide removal. Without
.B \-\-yes ,
an interactive confirmation is required; non-TTY sessions refuse to proceed.
